x4freetext: Numerical Data
The Energy in the Stack was Calculated According to
C.F.Williamson Et Al.,Cea-R3042(1966).
The Stacks were Irradiated For 6-10 Hours at Beam
Currents of 2-3 Microamperes.
Resolution 2.3 KeV at 1.33 MeV
The Error of the Cross Sections is Less Than
The Errors were Obtained by Compounding the Estimated
Errors of All Measured Quantities. No Further Details
Are Given
Lakw
Some Corrections have Been Included by
CAJAD
Err-Analys and Method are Corrected. Lower
Case.
V.Mc-Lane`S Remark is Included
Last checking has been done.
Independent
Independent
4.6% Isomeric Transition
Nd-148,Enriched to 95.44%, Thickness
0.25 to 0.45 Mg/Cm**2, Electrodeposited onto 0.012 mm
Thick Al-Foil. The Nd-Layer was Covered with Another
0.012 mm Al-Foil. Since the Conditions of the
Electrodeposition are not Unambiguously Reproducible,
The Absolute Amount of Nd in the Target was Determined
By Neutron Activation Analysis After the Irradiations
And Cross Section Measurements. Four or Fife Nd-Targets
Were Arranged to a Stack Interspersed by Al-Foils For
Energy Degradation.
. Experimental Isomeric Ratios are Compared to
Those Calculated in the Framework of the Statistical
Model. Spin Cutoff Parameters For the Level Density
Distribution and the Nuclear Moment of Inertia are
Deduced.
The Error in the Projectile Energy Varies
Between 1 and 10% Depending on the Position of the
Target Layer in the Foil Stack.
